Preconditions:
- The input integer n represents the number of members in a group.
- The input integer minProfit represents the minimum profit required for a scheme to be considered profitable.
- The input array group represents the number of members required for each scheme.
- The input array profit represents the profit generated by each scheme.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the number of schemes that can be chosen.
- The returned value is the number of schemes modulo 10^9 + 7.